{"word":"H3286 - יָעַף - yâʻaph - yaw-af' - Faint","slug":"H3286","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">יָעַף</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>yâʻaph"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>yaw-af'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Faint"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D9;&#x05E2;&#x05E3; - ya&#x0302;&#x201B;aph</b> - <i>yaw-af'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>tire</i> (as if from wearisome <i>flight</i>): - faint, cause to fly, (be) weary (self)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3287\">H3287</a>, <a href=\"#/H3288\">H3288</a>"}]}